First Lady Melania Trump held telephone calls with teachers and educators from across America in recognition of National Teacher Day and Teacher Appreciation Week. During the calls, Mrs. Trump expressed her appreciation for the efforts of educators during the coronavirus pandemic. They discussed topics such as distance learning methods, resources for low-income families, parent-teacher relationships, and challenges with distance learning. The First Lady was pleased to hear about innovative solutions being implemented by school faculty, families, and local governments. She commended the determination of educators and emphasized the importance of coming together to provide quality education during these challenging times.